    "text_1": {
      "type": "content-block",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_1": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Varley: The New Uniform of Casual Sophistication",
            "tag": "h2",
            "size": "h3",
            "font": "serif"
          }
        },
        "text_1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>There's a quiet shift happening in women's golfwear and Varley is at the center of it.</p><p>Originally known for redefining off-duty style through elevated athleisure, the London-meets-LA brand has steadily carved out space in the golf world. Not with bold logos or loud prints, but with clean lines, tonal palettes, and a level of understated polish that works just as well on the course as it does off.</p><p>At a glance, Varley isn't trying to be a golf brand. And that's precisely what makes it perfect for today's game.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_1",
        "text_1"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "alignment": "left",
        "enable_animation": true
      }
    },
